    <div id="progress">
        <h2>Retro Tavern's Journey</h2>
        <p>
            At first Retro Tavern was originally going to be an autobiography with a house kind of naming sense, 
            and a black and white theme. Meaning the pages would have been front door (homepage), bedroom (what 
            falls under Status on this site), kitchen (eating habits, likes and dislikes), living room (hobbies/past 
            times), and basement (what falls on workshop on this site). However, I scrapped the idea as I didn't 
            have a good grasp on who I was, what I like, and my traits. Ironic isn't it. I didn't know who I was, 
            yet <em>I knew who I was</em>. Technically, I still don't know myself to an extent, but I know enough 
            for viewers to get a basic understanding. Anyway, that was since the 25<sup>th</sup> May, 2022. After 
            I graduated from <abbr title="Antigua & Barbuda International Institute of Technology">ABIIT</abbr> I  
            restarted my project. However, this time I changed from an autobiography to the current portfolio site. 
            I started it on the 6<sup>th</sup> November, 2022. And I will be honest right now. I had no plan, and I 
            still don't. I am 100% winging it. Designs come into my head at the randomest of times, and as I am free 
            as a bird, I get to work when the thoughts designs appear. It can be right as I am about to go sleep or 
            as I just wake up.
            <br><br>
            Currently the site is being created with the help of the Javascript Framework called Astro. I originally 
            coded it the old fashion way in Visual Studio Code. That was until a good friend of mine introduced me to 
            Astro. It was what I hoped the future of programming would be. Different languages and framesworks combined 
            into one.
            <br><br>
            Down below are screenshots of the autobiography and the hard coded version.
        </p>
